The R3D License governs the use, distribution, and modification of any
three-dimensional rendering library published under this license. It is designed
to protect the rights of the original creator while granting developers
reasonable freedom to build, integrate, and distribute software products that
rely on 3D rendering technology.


Section 2. Definitions

"Software" refers to all source code, compiled binaries, shaders, rendering
pipelines, 3D assets, and documentation included in the distribution package
of this library.

"Creator" refers to the individual or entity holding the copyright over the
Software.

"User" refers to any individual or entity that obtains, uses, integrates, or
distributes the Software under the terms of this license.

"Derivative Work" refers to any software or product built in whole or in part
using the Software, including modifications, integrations, and ports to other
platforms or environments.


Section 3. Granted Rights

The Creator grants the User a non-exclusive, royalty-free right to use the
Software for personal, academic, and commercial purposes.

The User is permitted to integrate the Software into applications that make use
of three-dimensional features, including but not limited to XYZ spatial
transformations, perspective and orthographic projections, volumetric lighting,
3D textures, and geometry-based rendering pipelines.

The User is permitted to redistribute the Software as part of a finished
product, provided that this license document is included in full and without
modification.


Section 4. User Obligations

Any distribution of the Software or a Derivative Work must include a complete,
